{"key":"post-9862295","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9862295</id>\n<content>Use gypsum, but don't use the lime, since you don't need or want to pH adjust coir.&amp;nbsp; Add coffee grinds if you have them, or a small amount of composted chicken manure will also add a lot of bang.&amp;nbsp; Use no more than 5% chicken manure if you go that route(1/2 part to 10).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Never pressure cook bulk substrates.&amp;nbsp; It makes them far more likely to contaminate.&amp;nbsp; Simply hydrate the coir to field capacity and pasteurize at 60C to 70C for one hour, measured at the center of the substrate being heat treated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Make sure your popcorn spawn isn't contaminated.&amp;nbsp; It's extremely prone to bacteria contamination, especially when inoculated with untested LC.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9862438</next>\n<prev>9862262</prev>\n<first>9862034</first>\n<last>9952877</last>\n<when>1235588860</when>\n<utime>02/25/09 09:07 PM</utime>\n</post>"}